 GIT COMMANDS

1. git init = initialise git to monitor current repository.

2. rm -rf .git = disengage git monitoring.

3. git add (file) = tostat stage files and modifications to be noted by git.
	git add . = to stage all files at once.

4. git restore = restore modified changes before commit.

5. git log = to show history of git activity.

6. git status = to show the status.

7. git commit (file) = to save finalised changes.
	git commit -m = to commit and add comment.

8. git push origin main= to export to origin/github

9. git pull = to import from origin/github

10. git branch = to list branches
	git branch -d (branch) = to delete branch.
	git branch -m (branch name) = to change branch name.

11. git checkout (branch name) = to change branch
	git checkout -b (branch name) = to make a new branch.

12. git merge (temp branch) = to merge changes

13. git clone (link to remote repo) = to clone a remote git repo

